com.yantra.yfc.rcp

Class YRCContentAssistBindingData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yantra.yfc.rcp.YRCContentAssistBindingData

  • public class YRCContentAssistBindingData
extends java.lang.Object
    Instances of this class provide binding and behavioral information for providing content assist for text controls only.
    Content assist can be invoked on a text control by using the combination of the following keys: Ctrl + Space
    Example Code: // Create a text binding data. YRCTextBindingData txtBindingData = new YRCTextBindingData(); // Create a content assist binding data. YRCContentAssistBindingData contentAssistBindingObject = new YRCContentAssistBindingData(); // Set the repeating element path from where the content assist will pick up the data from. contentAssistBindingObject.setContentAssistBinding("SellerList:SellerList/Seller"); // Set the path to the code binding, this is the attribute value that will be set // onto the text control. contentAssistBindingObject.setCodeBinding("ID"); // Set the path to the description binding, this is the attribute value that will be displayed // on the content assist. contentAssistBindingObject.setDescriptionBinding("Name"); // The theme using which the content assit will be displayed. contentAssistBindingObject.setThemeBinding("Theme"); // Set the content assist onto the text binding data. txtBindingData.setContentAssistBindingObject(contentAssistBindingObject); // Set the text binding data onto the control. txtContentAssist.setData(YRCConstants.YRC_TEXT_BINDING_DEFINATION,txtBindingData);
    See Also:
    YRCContentAssistData, YRCPlatformUI.registerContentAssist(Text, YRCContentAssistData)
